If you love what I am doing, keep reading. ⬇️

I am trying my best to grow and get a website up so that I can share my designs, jewelry creations, sarcasm and love with you all! 

Many people have also asked for an app - which I would LOVE to create because, hell yes!! 
🥰🙌🏻
I think this is all incredibly amazing, and I want to bring it all to you, but it all costs money AND time! And I am a one woman, single mother crew!

With the type of content I am creating, I won't receive your typical monetization. No matter how many millions of views I receive because the content has profanity. 🤦‍♀️

Now, I really don't want to stop producing the content that you all love, I don't want to edit myself when I am not hurting anyone or being vulgar towards anyone and when this content is reaching so many people in such a positive way.

It is ALL peace, love and kindness over here.
❤️✌🏻

The messages I receive, the comments; I am absolutely overflowing with gratitude knowing that I can help even just one person through a bad day. 
🙏🏻

I am here to connect, make you smile, maybe even get out a laugh. I create to lift you up and help you stand strong. 
❤️💪🏻

So if you can, help a girl out! 🙏🏻
I have opened a Buy Me a Coffee Page, and being so new to all of this I am not sure where else to look. If you can please share my content, buy me a coffee, shoot me a message with your ideas - if you have any - on how to help me continue to grow while not sinking my own household ship financially.

There is a link to my Buy Me a Coffee Page in my VIP ☕❤️ 

And please, absolutely ZERO obligation here for ANYONE. I will create no matter what. 

I love and appreciate you ALL! 🥰✌🏻❤️🙌🏻

A little info, especially for those who snub their noses at the pentacle - misnaming it a pentagram - as if it is some sort of sign of 'evil' and why I choose to use it in my logo for Elements of Nature as the O in EON.

I won't get into how far back these symbols have been found and used but just give a bit of very basic information on what it represents.

Pentagram: is simply a regular five-pointed star. Yup, that's right, just a simple star.

In renaissance times the pentagram was associated to magic as a symbol. Attributing the five elements to the five points. Earth, Fire, Air, Water, & Spirit.

The pentagram was used in ancient Christian times as a symbol for the five senses, or the five wounds of Christ. 

Its current use is also a continuation of the ancient Babylonian use of the pentagram as a charm to protect against evil forces.
.
.
.
Pentacle: drawing a circle around the five-pointed star creates a similar symbol referred to as the pentacle and is used as a sign of life and connections.

The pentacle itself has been used in a variety of ways with a variety of shapes and I always suggest a little research into the history of symbols in general. Simply because it is actually very interesting to see common symbols used throughout history by many different cultures and belief systems.

Today I made myself a new Mala.
I call her '𝐏𝐚𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞'. 🇵🇸

If you've purchased from me or have been here for a while you know I work A LOT with stones. I am still learning to speak up and share HOW I work with stones so I thought this would be a perfect time as I made this for a specific reason.

𝗪𝗵𝘆 𝗱𝗼 𝗜 𝘄𝗲𝗮𝗿 𝗮 𝗠𝗮𝗹𝗮 - 𝙖𝙡𝙢𝙤𝙨𝙩 - 𝗱𝗮𝗶𝗹𝘆?
I wear a Mala that was created with an intention, I wear these throughout my day and different ones depending on the energy or activities of the day.

Sometimes this acts as an energy boost, or an extra bit of protection. Sometimes it's to calm, or to energize - depending on the stones used for the intention. But it stands as an aid and a reminder throughout the day. 

A reminder that I can get through times where I'm anxious.
A reminder to work through grief.
A reminder to keep myself centered when I know I'm going to be in a high energy place, etc. 

✴ I hold my Mala's a lot throughout the day.
✴ I meditate with them.
✴ I cleanse them as needed.
✴ I charge them on full moons . 

𝗪𝗵𝘆 𝗱𝗶𝗱 𝗜 𝗺𝗮𝗸𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗠𝗮𝗹𝗮?
The world has been in chaos, and I haven't - historically speaking - been one to speak up. I am timid, I am anxious, I am a hermit.
This Mala will act as a daily reminder for me to speak up. 

Many places in the world have been on my mind and heavy on my heart, but at this time Palestine has had the majority of my thoughts the last few weeks - yes, should have been much longer, but as I said, I haven't been one to dive into world issues. And I have been trying to change that. 

This Mala for me will act as a daily reminder that we are ALL human. That we all deserve love, care, and HUMAN RIGHTS! When I see my Mala throughout the day or hold it as I do so often, I can be  reminded and I can send out the energies of these stones to Palestine.

🖤 Black Onyx - grounding, strength, perseverance, and the ability to overcome challenges.

🤍 White Quartz - holds intention & peace.

❤️ Red Carnelian - motivation towards action.

💚 Green Aventurine - prosperity, success & independence.

🤍 Quartz Point - amplify healing.

You are in my heart ❤️🇵🇸
